    "hints": [
      "💡 İpucu 1: Önce deserialize (array → tree). Sonra recursive/iterative insert.",
      "💡 İpucu 2: Recursive: if val < node.val: node.left = insert(node.left, val) else: node.right = insert(node.right, val).",
      "💡 İpucu 3: Sonra tekrar serialize et (level-order)."
    ],
    "explanation": "BST Insert — deserialize, ekleme, serialize üçlüsü.\n\nclass Node:\n    def __init__(self, val, left=None, right=None):\n        self.val = val; self.left = left; self.right = right\n\ndef deserialize(arr):\n    if not arr or arr[0] is None: return None\n    root = Node(arr[0])\n    queue = deque([root])\n    i = 1\n    while queue and i < len(arr):\n        node = queue.popleft()\n        if i < len(arr) and arr[i] is not None:\n            node.left = Node(arr[i]); queue.append(node.left)\n        i += 1\n        if i < len(arr) and arr[i] is not None:\n            node.right = Node(arr[i]); queue.append(node.right)\n        i += 1\n    return root\n\ndef insert(node, val):\n    if not node: return Node(val)\n    if val < node.val: node.left = insert(node.left, val)\n    else: node.right = insert(node.right, val)\n    return node\n\nNeden deserialize/serialize? Test framework düz array bekliyor, kullanıcı kodu ise Node yapısı kullanıyor.",
