    "explanation": "Cycle Detection undirected graph'ta iki yöntem:\n\n1) DFS + parent:\nfrom collections import defaultdict\ndef has_cycle_undirected(n, edges):\n    graph = defaultdict(list)\n    for u, v in edges:\n        graph[u].append(v); graph[v].append(u)\n    visited = set()\n    def dfs(node, parent):\n        visited.add(node)\n        for neighbor in graph[node]:\n            if neighbor not in visited:\n                if dfs(neighbor, node): return True\n            elif neighbor != parent:\n                return True\n        return False\n    for i in range(n):\n        if i not in visited:\n            if dfs(i, -1): return True\n    return False\n\n2) Union-Find (daha kısa).\n\nMülakat notu: Union-Find bazı problemlerde DFS'ten temiz. İkisini de bil.",
    "complexity": "O(V + E)",
