    "title": "Linked List Ters Çevirme",
    "category": "algorithms",
    "level": "beginner",
    "description": "Bir singly linked list'i yerinde (in-place) ters çevir.\n\nGiriş formatı: Python list — [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n\nÖrnek: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] → [5, 4, 3, 2, 1]\n\nKısıt: O(n) zaman, O(1) bellek.",
    "starter_code": "class ListNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.next = next\n\ndef reverse_linked_list(head_arr: list) -> list:\n    # 1) List'i Node'lara çevir\n    # 2) Iterative: prev=None, curr=head. curr.next = prev; prev=curr; curr=next\n    # 3) Node'ları tekrar list'e çevir\n    pass",
    "test_cases": [
      {
        "input": [
          1,
          2,
          3,
          4,
          5
        ],
        "expected": [
          5,
          4,
          3,
          2,
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "input": [
          1,
          2
        ],
        "expected": [
          2,
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "input": [
          1
        ],
        "expected": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "input": [],
        "expected": []
      }
    ],
    "hints": [
      "💡 İpucu 1: Three pointers: prev=None, curr=head, while curr: next_node = curr.next; curr.next = prev; prev = curr; curr = next_node",
      "💡 İpucu 2: List→Node dönüşümü: ilk node head, sonrakiler .next",
      "💡 İpucu 3: Boş liste veya tek eleman özel durum"
    ],
    "explanation": "Reverse Linked List en temel pointer sorusu.\n\nclass ListNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n        self.val = val; self.next = next\n\ndef reverse_linked_list(head_arr):\n    # List to nodes\n    if not head_arr: return []\n    head = ListNode(head_arr[0])\n    curr = head\n    for v in head_arr[1:]:\n        curr.next = ListNode(v); curr = curr.next\n    # Reverse\n    prev, curr = None, head\n    while curr:\n        nxt = curr.next\n        curr.next = prev\n        prev = curr\n        curr = nxt\n    # Nodes to list\n    result = []\n    while prev:\n        result.append(prev.val); prev = prev.next\n    return result\n\nMülakat notu: Recursive vs iterative → Iterative O(1) bellek, recursive O(n) call stack.",
    "complexity": "O(n) zaman, O(1) bellek",
    "related_concepts": [
